{"type":"finding","id":"finding-s5-07-context-init-upsert","rank":1,"focus":"S5-07","summary":"Add a context init graph-seed step immediately after step_seed_frontier so frontier_slices_json becomes real SLICE/FILE/SYMBOL/DEPENDENCY nodes before the first sweep.","reference":{"repo":"loop-cli-main","file":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/manager.ts","lines":"34,38,43,49,69","mechanism":"Startup hydrates projects, saved loops, migration fields, task ids, controller options, and prior run state before controllers start."},"target":{"file":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","lines":"226-238,496-514","why":"The YAML already has code_graph_query frontier output but only upserts graph nodes after iteration output exists."},"portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win"}
{"type":"finding","id":"finding-s5-07-seed-provenance","rank":2,"focus":"S5-07","summary":"Persist per-node seed provenance and fallback confidence so code_graph_query seeds and Glob/Grep fallback seeds do not carry equal convergence authority.","reference":{"repo":"kasper","file":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/agent-prompt-resolver.ts","lines":"203,209,218,236,240","mechanism":"Prompt source resolution records a precedence chain across project/global config, file directives, inline prompts, and conventional file locations."},"target":{"file":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","lines":"237-238","why":"frontier_source is already tracked at event level; seeded node metadata should preserve the same provenance at graph level."},"portDifficulty":"easy","tag":"quick-win"}
{"type":"finding","id":"finding-s5-07-idempotent-seed-repair","rank":3,"focus":"S5-07","summary":"Add an explicit idempotent seed/repair path so duplicate or empty init seeds produce telemetry instead of surfacing later as an unexplained CONTINUE decision.","reference":{"repo":"kasper","file":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts","lines":"159,165,176,185,201,204","mechanism":"State init overlays defaults, repairs missing arrays/maps, restores dedupe sets, and rebuilds inconsistent running state before evaluation."},"target":{"file":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs","lines":"124-153","why":"Non-council upsert currently rejects empty node/edge batches; a seed mode should separate idempotent repair from malformed input."},"portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win"}
{"type":"finding","id":"finding-s5-07-review-file-seed","rank":4,"focus":"S5-07","summary":"Seed review with changed FILE nodes and hotspot metadata from structural impact before graph convergence, while keeping dependency seeding in context mode first.","reference":{"repo":"loop-cli-main","file":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/loop-cli-main/src/daemon/projects.ts","lines":"12,15,28,35,47,56,73","mechanism":"Project init migrates inventory, skips corrupt entries, loads valid items into a map, and creates a default inventory root when absent."},"target":{"file":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","lines":"483-496,1027-1040","why":"Review runs graph convergence before inline stop, but graph upsert only imports latest iteration graphEvents and skips empty graphEvents."},"portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win"}
